  <description type="morphology">Stems sparsely puberulent, often tomentulose proximal to heads. Leaves sparsely puberulent, not resinous. Involucres 8–12 mm. Phyllaries recurved, margins glandular (if at all), apices obtuse to acute, faces apically cinereous. Disc florets 9–16; corollas 9–10 mm. 2n = 10.</description>
  <description type="phenology">Flowering Jul–Oct.</description>
  <description type="habitat">Chaparral in foothills, coastal mountains, and islands, usually with Quercus, Pinus, Arctostaphylos, Rhus, Heteromeles, Adenostoma, Ceanothus;</description>
